Basic information
This project is an instant messaging platform.
This project is wrote in python 3.6, using PyCharm as the IDE.
This project has a gui for the client, using tkinter package for gui

########################################################################################################################
How to run
go to the project1 folder, open the terminal window and type commands to run server and client.

Sample command for server:
    python server.py 1500
you may need to use "python3" instead "python" if you have both python2 & 3 in your computer.
"1500" is the port number for server, you can change it

Sample command for client:
    python client.py DESKTOP-73DGQV2 1500 1600
you may need to use "python3" instead "python" if you have both python2 & 3 in your computer.
"DESKTOP-73DGQV2" is the hostname for server, you may change it according to the server you use. There is a commented
code in server.py line 13 which you can uncomment to print the server hostname
"1500" is the port number for server, it should be the same as the port number you give when run server
"1600" is the port number for client, you can change it

You can also change the _init_ function in server and client to set certain values to hostname and port number so that
you don't need to input them every time.

########################################################################################################################
List of files
server.py
    source code for server, including a Server class and code for running server
client.py
    source code for client, including a Client class and code for running client
users.csv
    a csv file to store the registered users, each line is a user, including username and password
README
    this file

########################################################################################################################
The user manual for client

When you run client, it will show a gui window. You can see a menu for register and login, and you can click the button.
Then, there will be a new window to ask you input username and password, they you can click submit button to submit it.
For register, there will be a message box to tell you whether you register success or not. For login, if fail, there
will be a message box tell you; if success, it will go to a new window and show a menu of operations you can choose.

The operations to choose after login including list, message and logout. If you click list, there will be a new window
to show you the username of active users. If you click message, there will be a new window to ask you input the username
of whom you want to send the message to and the message you want to send. Then you can click the submit button and
a message box will tell you whether you send it success or not. If you click logout, it will close the connection and
the gui window.

After you login, you are the active user and other users can see your name and send message to you. Once there is a
message come, there will be a message box pop up and tell you who send you what message.

For all input boxes, they can't be empty when you submit, otherwise there will be a error message box. There is a return
button for input windows and list window to help you return to the previous menu window.








